pullRequest.title: chore: improved accuracy of round() by more consistent use of tolerance. The latter is adjusted to be lower. JsonQueryProcessor now prints doubles up to scale of 12.

commit.message: chore: improved accuracy of round() by more consistent use of tolerance. The latter is adjusted to be lower. JsonQueryProcessor now prints doubles up to scale of 12.

nodes.bodyText: Do you think this change could fix the issue we are having with bound parameters and PGWire?
This change seems to be unrelated, was it added accidentally or it is on purpose?
